### 8. pytest_full_suite_passes — GREEN (was RED)
- Command: `cd activegraph && ../venv/bin/pytest -q --no-header`
- Result: `623 passed, 15 skipped in 15.55s`
- The sqlite I/O error in `tests/test_wheel_completeness.py` is gone.
- Root cause (per inspection of commit 67fa8da's quickstart.py diff): WAL
  sidecars (`.db-wal`, `.db-shm`) were left orphaned across test runs
  because `run_fixture_mode` only deleted the `.db` file and never closed
  the SQLite store. Subsequent calls (in-process tests, then the wheel
  subprocess) opened a fresh `.db` with `PRAGMA journal_mode=WAL`, which
  triggered recovery against a stale `.db-wal` and raised
  `OperationalError: disk I/O error` inside `_ensure_schema`. Fix in
  67fa8da adds `_remove_quickstart_db_files()` (clears all four suffixes)
  and wraps the runtime work in try/finally with `rt.graph.store.close()`.
- Confirms my first-eval hypothesis (leaked sqlite handles / WAL sidecar
  residue) was on the right track, though the contamination point was
  `cli/quickstart.py`, not the test fixtures themselves.

